# End of macro CWHEAD
a161			; | MONITOR ( -- ) Display system breakpoint/monitor | DONE 
a161			; | | At start the current various registers will be displayed with contents. 
a161			; | | Top right corner will show the most recent debug marker seen. 
a161			; | | The bottom of the screen will also show the values of the data stack pointer (DSP) 
a161			; | | and the return stack pointer (RSP). 
a161			; | | Pressing: 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    1 - Initial screen 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    2 - Display a data dump of HL 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    3 - Display a data dump of DE 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    4 - Display a data dump of BC 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    5 - Display a data dump of HL 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    6 - Display a data dump of DSP 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    7 - Display a data dump of RSP 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    8 - Display a data dump of what is at DSP 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    9 - Display a data dump of what is at RSP 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    0 - Exit monitor and continue running. This will also enable break points 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    * - Disable break points 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | |    # - Enter traditional monitor mode 
a161			; | |  
a161			; | | 
a161			; | | Monitor Mode 
a161			; | | ------------ 
a161			; | | A prompt of '>' will be shown for various commands: 
